script:
Take a look at the following facts about a fictional world:

In the fictional world of Eldoria, magic is powered by the energy of stardust.
The Great War of Eldoria was fought between the kingdoms of Luminaria and Shadowmere.
Dragons in Eldoria are revered as ancient beings and guardians of wisdom.
The capital city of Eldoria, Astralara, floats in the sky thanks to an enchanted crystal core.
The forbidden Black Forest in Eldoria is home to mysterious creatures known as the Shadowstalkers.
The legendary sword Excaliburin Eldoria can only be wielded by the rightful heir to the throne.
The Order of the Silver Crescent in Eldoria is a group of elite knights sworn to protect the realm from dark forces.
In Eldoria, the annual Moon Festival is a celebration of unity between the kingdoms and the lunar magic that binds them.
The Library of Alexandria in Eldoria holds ancient tomes that contain forgotten knowledge and powerful spells.
The last known descendant of the ancient High Elves in Eldoria is rumored to possess the gift of foresight.
Look, about the fictional world... What is the source of magic in Eldoria?
One question about the fictional world. Which kingdoms were involved in the Great War of Eldoria?
Going back to the fictional world, How are dragons viewed in the world of Eldoria?
Look, about the fictional world... What keeps the capital city of Astralara afloat?
Going back to the fictional world, What resides in the forbidden Black Forest of Eldoria?
Answer this question about the fictional world: Who can wield the legendary sword Excalibur in Eldoria?
Look, about the fictional world... What is the purpose of the Order of the Silver Crescent in Eldoria?
Look, about the fictional world... What does the Moon Festival celebrate in Eldoria?
Going back to the fictional world, What secrets are stored in the Library of Alexandria in Eldoria?
One question about the fictional world. What special ability is rumored to belong to the last High Elf descendant in Eldoria?
